author: Ariel Zilber For Dailymail.Com
title: Trumps land in Washington after weekend of golf diplomacy | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad The Trumps land in Washington after a weekend of golf diplomacy with Japan's prime minister as Ivanka posts photo of her kids playing at Mar-a-Lago on Instagram President Donald Trump and his family boarded Air Force One and returned to Washington after a busy weekend at Mar-a-Lago in Florida Trump played host to the Japanese prime minister, Shinzo Abe, and his wife Joining Trump on Air Force One were his daughter, Ivanka Trump, son-in-law Jared Kushner, and their three children White House strategist Steve Bannon and National Security Adviser Michael Flynn were also seen deplaning Air Force One Flynn is reported to be on thin ice after it was revealed he misled the administration when he denied talking to the Russian ambassador to the US about lifting sanctions against Moscow in December Published: 03:27 GMT, 13 February 2017 | Updated: 04:36 GMT, 13 February 2017 260 shares
